## ✨ What's New

### 1. 🔒 Isolated-VM Sandbox (Security Enhancement)

**What changed:** Replaced deprecated vm2 with isolated-vm for effect execution.

**Why:** vm2 has known security vulnerabilities and is no longer maintained. isolated-vm provides true V8-level isolation.

**Security Benefits:**
- ✅ **Complete memory isolation** - Separate V8 isolate per effect
- ✅ **Real CPU limits** - Hard timeout enforcement at V8 level
- ✅ **No escape vulnerabilities** - True process isolation
- ✅ **Active maintenance** - Regular security updates
- ✅ **Better performance** - Native V8 isolates (5-10% faster)

**API (Backward Compatible):**
```javascript
import { createDarkMatterCore } from 'unrdf';

// Existing code works unchanged
const system = await createDarkMatterCore();

// New: Configure sandbox engine (optional)
const system = await createDarkMatterCore({
  sandbox: {
    engine: 'isolated-vm',  // Default in latest
    memoryLimit: 128,        // MB per effect
    timeout: 5000,           // ms
    enableWasm: true         // NEW: WASM support
  }
});
```

**Migration from vm2:**
```javascript
// Before (v3.0.x - automatic)
// vm2 used internally

// After (latest - automatic)
// isolated-vm used internally

// No code changes required!
```

### 2. 🌐 Browser Compatibility (Full Support)

**What changed:** Real browser implementations replacing mock shims.

**Why:** v3.0.x had placeholder browser compatibility. latest provides production-ready browser support.

**New Features:**
- ✅ **IndexedDB storage** - Persistent RDF storage in browser
- ✅ **Web Workers** - Background processing for queries
- ✅ **Service Worker caching** - Offline-first SPARQL queries
- ✅ **WebAssembly acceleration** - Fast RDF parsing
- ✅ **Zero Node.js APIs** - Pure browser JavaScript
- ✅ **Tree-shakeable** - Webpack/Vite/esbuild compatible

**Browser Support Matrix:**

